alaSaaCtrlTable.name: alaSaaCtrlTable
alaSaaCtrlTable.description: Defines the SAA control table for providing, via SNMP, the capability of performing SAA test operations.

alaSaaCtrlEntry.name: alaSaaCtrlEntry
alaSaaCtrlEntry.description: An entry in the alaSaaCtrlTable table, containing information on the Saa function for a single instance of the Saa.

alaSaaCtrlOwnerIndex.name: alaSaaCtrlOwnerIndex
alaSaaCtrlOwnerIndex.description: Owner name to identify the responsiblity of the entries in the table.

alaSaaCtrlTestIndex.name: alaSaaCtrlTestIndex
alaSaaCtrlTestIndex.description: Unique name to identify the entries in the table. The name is unique across various SNMP users.

alaSaaCtrlRowStatus.name: alaSaaCtrlRowStatus
alaSaaCtrlRowStatus.description: This object allows entries to be created and deleted in the table.

alaSaaCtrlDescr.name: alaSaaCtrlDescr
alaSaaCtrlDescr.description: User provided description string for the SAA.

alaSaaCtrlAdminStatus.name: alaSaaCtrlAdminStatus
alaSaaCtrlAdminStatus.description: Indicates wether to start or stop the SAA test.

alaSaaCtrlTestMode.name: alaSaaCtrlTestMode
alaSaaCtrlTestMode.description: The type of SAA test to be performed. The undefined value corresponds to the case when an entry is created in the alaSaaCtrlTable table without specifying a value for this object. This value shall be updated when the user creates an entry for the corresponding saa in the alaSaaIpCtrlTable table, alaSaaEthoamCtrlTable table or alaSaaMacCtrlTable table.

alaSaaCtrlRuns.name: alaSaaCtrlRuns
alaSaaCtrlRuns.description: Indicates number of times SAA test has been executed.

alaSaaCtrlFailures.name: alaSaaCtrlFailures
alaSaaCtrlFailures.description: Indicates the number of times this SAA test has failed.

alaSaaCtrlLastRunResult.name: alaSaaCtrlLastRunResult
alaSaaCtrlLastRunResult.description: The result of the latest SAA test iteration.

alaSaaCtrlLastRunTime.name: alaSaaCtrlLastRunTime
alaSaaCtrlLastRunTime.description: The time at which the last iteration of the SAA was run.

alaSaaCtrlInterval.name: alaSaaCtrlInterval
alaSaaCtrlInterval.description: Interval, in minutes, between two iterations of the SAA test. Valid values are 1, 2, 5 and 10-1500.

alaSaaCtrlStartAt.name: alaSaaCtrlStartAt
alaSaaCtrlStartAt.description: Specifies the time at which the SAA test is to be started. The deci-seconds specified in DateAndTime has no significance in scheduling SAA. The year in DateAndTime must be in the range from 1970 to 2037.

alaSaaCtrlStopAt.name: alaSaaCtrlStopAt
alaSaaCtrlStopAt.description: Specifies the time at which the SAA test is to be stopped.Special value for DataAndTime which is 9999-12-31,23:59:59.0 is used to reset the existing configured value of this object, indicating that the SAA test should never stop. The deci-seconds in the DateAndTime has no significance in scheduling SAA.The year in DateAndTime must be in the range from 1970 to 2037.

alaSaaCtrlMaxHistoryRows.name: alaSaaCtrlMaxHistoryRows
alaSaaCtrlMaxHistoryRows.description: Specifies the maximum number of iterations for which history data is maintained.

alaSaaCtrlJitterThreshold.name: alaSaaCtrlJitterThreshold
alaSaaCtrlJitterThreshold.description: Trap is generated when the Jitter Threshold is crossed. 0 indicates it is diabled.

alaSaaCtrlRTTThreshold.name: alaSaaCtrlRTTThreshold
alaSaaCtrlRTTThreshold.description: Trap is generated when the RTT Threshold is crossed. 0 indicates it is diabled.

alaSaaIpCtrlTable.name: alaSaaIpCtrlTable
alaSaaIpCtrlTable.description: It defines the ping Control Table for providing the ping capability via SNMP. The results of these tests are stored in the alaSaaIpResultsTable and alaSaaIpHistoryTable.

alaSaaIpCtrlOwnerIndex.name: alaSaaIpCtrlOwnerIndex
alaSaaIpCtrlOwnerIndex.description: Owner name to identify the responsiblity of the entries in the table.

alaSaaIpCtrlTestIndex.name: alaSaaIpCtrlTestIndex
alaSaaIpCtrlTestIndex.description: Unique name to identify the entries in the table. This name is unique across various SNMP users.

alaSaaIpCtrlRowStatus.name: alaSaaIpCtrlRowStatus
alaSaaIpCtrlRowStatus.description: Allows entries to be created and deleted in the table. createAndWait value is not supported for this object.

alaSaaIpCtrlTestMode.name: alaSaaIpCtrlTestMode
alaSaaIpCtrlTestMode.description: Specifies the type of ping test defined by this entry.

alaSaaIpCtrlTgtAddrType.name: alaSaaIpCtrlTgtAddrType
alaSaaIpCtrlTgtAddrType.description: Specifies the InetAddress type of host address to be used as the destination for performing a ping operation. InetAddressIPv4(1) is the only type currently supported.

alaSaaIpCtrlTgtAddress.name: alaSaaIpCtrlTgtAddress
alaSaaIpCtrlTgtAddress.description: Specifies the IP host address to be used as the destination for performing a ping operation.

alaSaaIpCtrlSrcAddrType.name: alaSaaIpCtrlSrcAddrType
alaSaaIpCtrlSrcAddrType.description: Specifies the InetAddress type of host address to be used as the source for performing a ping operation. InetAddressIPv4(1) is the only type currently supported.

alaSaaIpCtrlSrcAddress.name: alaSaaIpCtrlSrcAddress
alaSaaIpCtrlSrcAddress.description: Specifies the IP host address to be used as the source for performing a ping operation. The default value of this object is 0.0.0.0 if alaSaaIpCtrlSrcAddrType is set to ipv4.

alaSaaIpCtrlPayloadSize.name: alaSaaIpCtrlPayloadSize
alaSaaIpCtrlPayloadSize.description: Specifies the size of the ICMP payload to be used for the ping operation.

alaSaaIpCtrlNumPkts.name: alaSaaIpCtrlNumPkts
alaSaaIpCtrlNumPkts.description: Specifies the number of packets to be sent in one ping iteration.Configuration of number of packets and inter packet delay should be such that total execution time remains less then 10s.

alaSaaIpCtrlInterPktDelay.name: alaSaaIpCtrlInterPktDelay
alaSaaIpCtrlInterPktDelay.description: Specifies the delay between two consecutive packets transmitted during a ping iteration.The value specified should be a multiple of 100.

alaSaaIpCtrlVRFId.name: alaSaaIpCtrlVRFId
alaSaaIpCtrlVRFId.description: Specifies the VRF ID. Only the value '0' is currently supported.

alaSaaIpCtrlTotalPktsSent.name: alaSaaIpCtrlTotalPktsSent
alaSaaIpCtrlTotalPktsSent.description: Specifies the total number of packets sent during all the ping iterations.

alaSaaIpCtrlTotalPktsRcvd.name: alaSaaIpCtrlTotalPktsRcvd
alaSaaIpCtrlTotalPktsRcvd.description: Specifies the total number of packets received during all the ping iterations.

alaSaaIpCtrlMinRTT.name: alaSaaIpCtrlMinRTT
alaSaaIpCtrlMinRTT.description: Specifies the minimum round trip time among all the iterations of the SAA.

alaSaaIpCtrlAvgRTT.name: alaSaaIpCtrlAvgRTT
alaSaaIpCtrlAvgRTT.description: Specifies the average round trip time of all the iterations of the SAA.

alaSaaIpCtrlMaxRTT.name: alaSaaIpCtrlMaxRTT
alaSaaIpCtrlMaxRTT.description: Specifies the maximum round trip time among all the iterations of the SAA.

alaSaaIpCtrlMinJitter.name: alaSaaIpCtrlMinJitter
alaSaaIpCtrlMinJitter.description: Specifies the minimum jitter among all the iterations of the SAA.

alaSaaIpCtrlAvgJitter.name: alaSaaIpCtrlAvgJitter
alaSaaIpCtrlAvgJitter.description: Specifies the average jitter of all the iterations of the SAA.

alaSaaIpCtrlMaxJitter.name: alaSaaIpCtrlMaxJitter
alaSaaIpCtrlMaxJitter.description: Specifies the maximum jitter among all the iterations of the SAA.

alaSaaIpCtrlTSMinRTT.name: alaSaaIpCtrlTSMinRTT
alaSaaIpCtrlTSMinRTT.description: Specifies the timestamp of the iteration that gave the minimum packet delay.

alaSaaIpCtrlTSMaxRTT.name: alaSaaIpCtrlTSMaxRTT
alaSaaIpCtrlTSMaxRTT.description: Specifies the timestamp of the iteration that gave the maximum packet delay.

alaSaaIpCtrlTSMinJitter.name: alaSaaIpCtrlTSMinJitter
alaSaaIpCtrlTSMinJitter.description: Specifies the timestamp of the iteration that gave the minimum packet jitter.

alaSaaIpCtrlTSMaxJitter.name: alaSaaIpCtrlTSMaxJitter
alaSaaIpCtrlTSMaxJitter.description: Specifies the timestamp of the iteration that gave the maximum packet jitter.

alaSaaIpResultsTable.name: alaSaaIpResultsTable
alaSaaIpResultsTable.description: Defines the IP Results Table for providing the capability of performing IP Ping operations. The results of these operations are stored in the alaSaaIpResultsTable and the alaSaaIpHistoryTable. An entry is removed from the alaSaaIpResultsTable when its corresponding alaSaaCtrlEntry is deleted.

alaSaaIpResultsEntry.name: alaSaaIpResultsEntry
alaSaaIpResultsEntry.description: Entry for the alaSaaResults table. An entry in this table summarizes results from multiple invocations of the test configured by the corresponding entry in alaSaaIpCtrlTable.

alaSaaIpResultsTestRunIndex.name: alaSaaIpResultsTestRunIndex
alaSaaIpResultsTestRunIndex.description: The value of alaSaaIpResultsTestRunIndex identifies the row entry that reports results for a single OAM test run. The value of this object starts from 1 and can go upto a maximum of alaSaaCtrlMaxHistoryRows.

alaSaaIpResultsPktsSent.name: alaSaaIpResultsPktsSent
alaSaaIpResultsPktsSent.description: Specifies the number of packets sent during a single ping iteration.

alaSaaIpResultsPktsRcvd.name: alaSaaIpResultsPktsRcvd
alaSaaIpResultsPktsRcvd.description: Specifies the number of packets received during a single ping iteration.

alaSaaIpResultsInterPktDelay.name: alaSaaIpResultsInterPktDelay
alaSaaIpResultsInterPktDelay.description: Specifies the inter-packet-delay with which the packets were sent in the iteration.

alaSaaIpResultsRunResultReason.name: alaSaaIpResultsRunResultReason
alaSaaIpResultsRunResultReason.description: If the iteration fails, this field indicates the reason for failure. If the reason for failure cannot be determined the value of this field is the string Unknown. For successful iterations, the value of this field is the string 'Iteration successful'.

alaSaaIpResultsRunTime.name: alaSaaIpResultsRunTime
alaSaaIpResultsRunTime.description: The date and time at which the iteraton was run.

alaSaaIpHistoryTable.name: alaSaaIpHistoryTable
alaSaaIpHistoryTable.description: It is the table for storing the results of a ping operation. An entry in this table is created when a ping operation is performed. Entries are removed from this table when its corresponding alaSaaCtrlEntry is deleted.

alaSaaIpHistoryIndex.name: alaSaaIpHistoryIndex
alaSaaIpHistoryIndex.description: An entry in this table is created when the result of a ping iteration is determined. The initial 2 instance identifier index values identify the alaSaaIpPingCtrlEntry that a ping iteration result (alaSaaIpHistoryEntry) belongs to. The alaSaaIpHistoryIndex element selects a single ping iteration result. The value of this object starts from 1 and can go up to 20,history of first 20 packets will be stored.

alaSaaIpHistoryPktRTT.name: alaSaaIpHistoryPktRTT
alaSaaIpHistoryPktRTT.description: The round trip time taken by a single packet in an iteration.

alaSaaIpHistoryPktJitter.name: alaSaaIpHistoryPktJitter
alaSaaIpHistoryPktJitter.description: The jitter value for a single packet in an iteration.

alaSaaEthoamCtrlTable.name: alaSaaEthoamCtrlTable
alaSaaEthoamCtrlTable.description: Defines the table for providing, via SNMP, the capability of performing Ethernet Loopback and DMM test operations. The results of these tests are stored in the alaSaaEthoamResultsTable and the alaSaaEthoamHistoryTable.

alaSaaEthoamCtrlEntry.name: alaSaaEthoamCtrlEntry
alaSaaEthoamCtrlEntry.description: Defines an entry in the alaSaaEthoamCtrlTable.

alaSaaEthoamCtrlOwnerIndex.name: alaSaaEthoamCtrlOwnerIndex
alaSaaEthoamCtrlOwnerIndex.description: Owner name to identify the responsiblity of the entries in the table.

alaSaaEthoamCtrlTestIndex.name: alaSaaEthoamCtrlTestIndex
alaSaaEthoamCtrlTestIndex.description: Unique name to identify the entries in the table. This name is unique across various SNMP users.

alaSaaEthoamCtrlRowStatus.name: alaSaaEthoamCtrlRowStatus
alaSaaEthoamCtrlRowStatus.description: This object allows entries to be created and deleted in the alaSaaEthoamCtrlTable. Deletion of an entry in this table results in all corresponding (same alaSaaEthoamCtrlOwnerIndex and alaSaaEthoamCtrlTestIndex index values) alaSaaEthoamResultsTable and alaSaaEthoamHistoryTable entries being deleted.

alaSaaEthoamCtrlTestMode.name: alaSaaEthoamCtrlTestMode
alaSaaEthoamCtrlTestMode.description: Specifies the type of Ethernet OAM test defined by this entry. ethernetLoopback - tests connectivity and round trip time by sending loopback requests. ethernetDmm - tests connectivity and round trip time by sending timestamped packets.

alaSaaEthoamCtrlTgtMepId.name: alaSaaEthoamCtrlTgtMepId
alaSaaEthoamCtrlTgtMepId.description: The Mep-Id of the destination to which the Ethernet Loopback or DMM message is to be sent. Either alaSaaEthoamCtrlTgtMepId or alaSaaEthoamCtrlTgtMAC should be specified while configuring an alaSaaEthoamCtrlEntry.

alaSaaEthoamCtrlTgtMAC.name: alaSaaEthoamCtrlTgtMAC
alaSaaEthoamCtrlTgtMAC.description: The Target MAC Address of the destination to which the Ethernet Loopback or DMM message is to be sent: A unicast destination MAC address. Either alaSaaEthoamCtrlTgtMepId or alaSaaEthoamCtrlTgtMAC should be specified while configuring an alaSaaEthoamCtrlEntry.

alaSaaEthoamCtrlSrcMepId.name: alaSaaEthoamCtrlSrcMepId
alaSaaEthoamCtrlSrcMepId.description: The Mep-Id of the source node initiating the Ethernet Loopback or DMM message.

alaSaaEthoamCtrlDomainName.name: alaSaaEthoamCtrlDomainName
alaSaaEthoamCtrlDomainName.description: The name of the domain to which the source Mep belongs.

alaSaaEthoamCtrlAssociationName.name: alaSaaEthoamCtrlAssociationName
alaSaaEthoamCtrlAssociationName.description: The name of the association in the domain (specified by alaSaaEthoamCtrlDomainName) to which the source Mep belongs.

alaSaaEthoamCtrlPktTimeOut.name: alaSaaEthoamCtrlPktTimeOut
alaSaaEthoamCtrlPktTimeOut.description: The maximum time to wait for the reply of the transmitted packet.

alaSaaEthoamCtrlNumPkts.name: alaSaaEthoamCtrlNumPkts
alaSaaEthoamCtrlNumPkts.description: The number of packets to be sent in one iteration of Eth-LB/DMM test.Configuration of number of packets and inter packet delay should be such that total execution time remains less then 10s.

alaSaaEthoamCtrlInterPktDelay.name: alaSaaEthoamCtrlInterPktDelay
alaSaaEthoamCtrlInterPktDelay.description: Specifies the delay between two consecutive packets transmitted during an iteration. The value specified should be a multiple of 100.

alaSaaEthoamCtrlPktData.name: alaSaaEthoamCtrlPktData
alaSaaEthoamCtrlPktData.description: An arbitrary amount of data to be included in the Data TLV, if the Data TLV is selected to be sent.

alaSaaEthoamCtrlVlanPriority.name: alaSaaEthoamCtrlVlanPriority
alaSaaEthoamCtrlVlanPriority.description: Priority. 3 bit value to be used in the VLAN tag, if present in the transmitted frame.

alaSaaEthoamCtrlDropEligible.name: alaSaaEthoamCtrlDropEligible
alaSaaEthoamCtrlDropEligible.description: Drop Enable bit value to be used in the VLAN tag, if present in the transmitted frame.

alaSaaEthoamCtrlTotalPktsRcvd.name: alaSaaEthoamCtrlTotalPktsRcvd
alaSaaEthoamCtrlTotalPktsRcvd.description: Specifies the total number of packets received during all the Eth-LB/DMM iterations.

alaSaaEthoamCtrlTotalPktsSent.name: alaSaaEthoamCtrlTotalPktsSent
alaSaaEthoamCtrlTotalPktsSent.description: Specifies the total number of packets sent during all the Eth-LB/DMM iterations.

alaSaaEthoamCtrlMinRTT.name: alaSaaEthoamCtrlMinRTT
alaSaaEthoamCtrlMinRTT.description: Specifies the minimum round trip time among all the iterations of the SAA.

alaSaaEthoamCtrlAvgRTT.name: alaSaaEthoamCtrlAvgRTT
alaSaaEthoamCtrlAvgRTT.description: Specifies the average round trip time of all the iterations of the SAA.

alaSaaEthoamCtrlMaxRTT.name: alaSaaEthoamCtrlMaxRTT
alaSaaEthoamCtrlMaxRTT.description: Specifies the maximum round trip time among all the iterations of the SAA.

alaSaaEthoamCtrlMinJitter.name: alaSaaEthoamCtrlMinJitter
alaSaaEthoamCtrlMinJitter.description: Specifies the minimum jitter among all the iterations of the SAA.

alaSaaEthoamCtrlAvgJitter.name: alaSaaEthoamCtrlAvgJitter
alaSaaEthoamCtrlAvgJitter.description: Specifies the average jitter of all the iterations of the SAA.

alaSaaEthoamCtrlMaxJitter.name: alaSaaEthoamCtrlMaxJitter
alaSaaEthoamCtrlMaxJitter.description: Specifies the maximum jitter among all the iterations of the SAA.

alaSaaEthoamCtrlTSMinRTT.name: alaSaaEthoamCtrlTSMinRTT
alaSaaEthoamCtrlTSMinRTT.description: The timestamp of the iteration that gave the minimum packet delay.

alaSaaEthoamCtrlTSMaxRTT.name: alaSaaEthoamCtrlTSMaxRTT
alaSaaEthoamCtrlTSMaxRTT.description: The timestamp of the iteration that gave the maximum packet delay.

alaSaaEthoamCtrlTSMinJitter.name: alaSaaEthoamCtrlTSMinJitter
alaSaaEthoamCtrlTSMinJitter.description: The timestamp of the iteration that gave the minimum packet jitter.

alaSaaEthoamCtrlTSMaxJitter.name: alaSaaEthoamCtrlTSMaxJitter
alaSaaEthoamCtrlTSMaxJitter.description: The timestamp of the iteration that gave the maximum packet jitter.

alaSaaEthoamResultsTable.name: alaSaaEthoamResultsTable
alaSaaEthoamResultsTable.description: Defines the Ethoam Results Table for providing the capability of performing Eth-LB/DMM operations. The results of these operations are stored in the alaSaaEthoamResultsTable and the alaSaaEthoamHistoryTable. An entry is removed from the alaSaaEthoamResultsTable when its corresponding alaSaaCtrlEntry is deleted.

alaSaaEthoamResultsEntry.name: alaSaaEthoamResultsEntry
alaSaaEthoamResultsEntry.description: Defines an entry in the alaSaaEthoamResultsTable. The alaSaaEthoamResultsTable has the same indexing as the alaSaaEthoamCtrlTable in order for a alaSaaEthoamResultsEntry to correspond to the alaSaaEthoamCtrlEntry that caused it to be created. An entry in this table summarizes results from multiple invocations of the test configured by the corresponding entry in alaSaaEthoamCtrlTable.

alaSaaEthoamResultsTestRunIndex.name: alaSaaEthoamResultsTestRunIndex
alaSaaEthoamResultsTestRunIndex.description: The value of alaSaaEthoamResultsTestRunIndex identifies the row entry that reports results for a single Eth-LB/DMM test run. The value of this object starts from 1 and can go upto a maximum of alaSaaCtrlMaxHistoryRows.

alaSaaEthoamResultsPktsSent.name: alaSaaEthoamResultsPktsSent
alaSaaEthoamResultsPktsSent.description: Specifies the number of packets sent during a single Eth-LB/DMM iteration.

alaSaaEthoamResultsPktsRcvd.name: alaSaaEthoamResultsPktsRcvd
alaSaaEthoamResultsPktsRcvd.description: Specifies the number of packets received during a single Eth-LB/DMM iteration

alaSaaEthoamResultsInterPktDelay.name: alaSaaEthoamResultsInterPktDelay
alaSaaEthoamResultsInterPktDelay.description: Specifies the inter-packet-delay with which the packets were sent in the iteration.

alaSaaEthoamResultsRunResult.name: alaSaaEthoamResultsRunResult
alaSaaEthoamResultsRunResult.description: The result of the Eth-LB/DMM iteration.

alaSaaEthoamResultsRunResultReason.name: alaSaaEthoamResultsRunResultReason
alaSaaEthoamResultsRunResultReason.description: If the iteration fails, this field indicates the reason for failure. If the reason for failure cannot be determined the value of this field is the string Unknown. For successful iterations, the value of this field is the string 'Iteration successful'.

alaSaaEthoamResultsRunTime.name: alaSaaEthoamResultsRunTime
alaSaaEthoamResultsRunTime.description: The date and time at which the iteraton was run.

alaSaaEthoamHistoryTable.name: alaSaaEthoamHistoryTable
alaSaaEthoamHistoryTable.description: Defines a table for storing the results of an Eth-LB/DMM iteration. The number of entries in this table for a configured test are limited by the value of the corresponding alaSaaCtrlMaxHistoryRows object. An entry in this table is created when the result of an Eth-LB/DMM test is determined. An entry is removed from this table when its corresponding alaSaaEthoamCtrlEntry is deleted. The agent removes the oldest entry for a test in the alaSaaEthoamHistoryTable to allow the addition of a new entry for that test once the number of rows in the alaSaaEthoamHistoryTable reaches the value specified by alaSaaCtrlMaxHistoryRows.

alaSaaEthoamHistoryIndex.name: alaSaaEthoamHistoryIndex
alaSaaEthoamHistoryIndex.description: An entry in this table is created when the result of an Eth-LB/DMM iteration is determined. The initial 2 instance identifier index values identify the alaSaaEthoamCtrlEntry that an Eth-LB/DMM iteration result (alaSaaEthoamHistoryEntry) belongs to. The alaSaaEthoamHistoryIndex element selects a single ping iteration result. The value of this object starts from 1 and can go up to 20,history of first 20 packets will be stored.

alaSaaEthoamHistoryPktRTT.name: alaSaaEthoamHistoryPktRTT
alaSaaEthoamHistoryPktRTT.description: The round trip time taken by a single packet in an iteration.

alaSaaEthoamHistoryPktJitter.name: alaSaaEthoamHistoryPktJitter
alaSaaEthoamHistoryPktJitter.description: The jitter value for a single packet in an iteration.

alaSaaMacCtrlTable.name: alaSaaMacCtrlTable
alaSaaMacCtrlTable.description: It defines the MAC-Ping Control Table for providing the ping capability via SNMP. The results of these tests are stored in the alaSaaMacResultsTable and alaSaaMacHistoryTable.

alaSaaMacCtrlOwnerIndex.name: alaSaaMacCtrlOwnerIndex
alaSaaMacCtrlOwnerIndex.description: Owner name to identify the responsiblity of the entries in the table.

alaSaaMacCtrlTestIndex.name: alaSaaMacCtrlTestIndex
alaSaaMacCtrlTestIndex.description: Unique name to identify the entries in the table. This name is unique across various SNMP users.

alaSaaMacCtrlRowStatus.name: alaSaaMacCtrlRowStatus
alaSaaMacCtrlRowStatus.description: Allows entries to be created and deleted in the table. createAndWait value is not supported for this object.

alaSaaMacCtrlDstAddress.name: alaSaaMacCtrlDstAddress
alaSaaMacCtrlDstAddress.description: Specifies the mac address to be used as the destination for performing a MAC-Ping operation.

alaSaaMacCtrlVlan.name: alaSaaMacCtrlVlan
alaSaaMacCtrlVlan.description: The 12 bit Vlan value to be used in the VLAN tag, in the transmitted frame.

alaSaaMacCtrlVlanPriority.name: alaSaaMacCtrlVlanPriority
alaSaaMacCtrlVlanPriority.description: Priority. 3 bit value to be used in the VLAN tag, if present in the transmitted frame.

alaSaaMacCtrlIsid.name: alaSaaMacCtrlIsid
alaSaaMacCtrlIsid.description: The i-domain Service Indentifier (I-SID) which identifies the service instance in a PBB network on a BEB switch. For a customer packet flowing toward the b-domain, the I-SID is derived from the VFI and inserted into the packet. For a packet arrived from the b-domain, the I-SID is used to identify the VFI for the i-domain processing. From the service MIB.

alaSaaMacCtrlPktData.name: alaSaaMacCtrlPktData
alaSaaMacCtrlPktData.description: An arbitrary amount of data to be included in the Data TLV, if the Data TLV is selected to be sent.

alaSaaMacCtrlDropEligible.name: alaSaaMacCtrlDropEligible
alaSaaMacCtrlDropEligible.description: Drop Enable bit value to be used in the VLAN tag, if present in the transmitted frame.

alaSaaMacCtrlPayloadSize.name: alaSaaMacCtrlPayloadSize
alaSaaMacCtrlPayloadSize.description: Specifies the size of the MAC-Ping payload to be used for the MAC-Ping operation.

alaSaaMacCtrlNumPkts.name: alaSaaMacCtrlNumPkts
alaSaaMacCtrlNumPkts.description: Specifies the number of packets to be sent in one MAC-Ping iteration.Configuration of number of packets and inter packet delay should be such that total execution time remains less then 10s.

alaSaaMacCtrlInterPktDelay.name: alaSaaMacCtrlInterPktDelay
alaSaaMacCtrlInterPktDelay.description: Specifies the delay between two consecutive packets transmitted during a MAC-Ping iteration.The value specified should be a multiple of 100.

alaSaaMacCtrlTotalPktsSent.name: alaSaaMacCtrlTotalPktsSent
alaSaaMacCtrlTotalPktsSent.description: Specifies the total number of packets sent during all the ping iterations.

alaSaaMacCtrlTotalPktsRcvd.name: alaSaaMacCtrlTotalPktsRcvd
alaSaaMacCtrlTotalPktsRcvd.description: Specifies the total number of packets received during all the ping iterations.

alaSaaMacCtrlMinRTT.name: alaSaaMacCtrlMinRTT
alaSaaMacCtrlMinRTT.description: Specifies the minimum round trip time among all the iterations of the SAA.

alaSaaMacCtrlAvgRTT.name: alaSaaMacCtrlAvgRTT
alaSaaMacCtrlAvgRTT.description: Specifies the average round trip time of all the iterations of the SAA.

alaSaaMacCtrlMaxRTT.name: alaSaaMacCtrlMaxRTT
alaSaaMacCtrlMaxRTT.description: Specifies the maximum round trip time among all the iterations of the SAA.

alaSaaMacCtrlMinJitter.name: alaSaaMacCtrlMinJitter
alaSaaMacCtrlMinJitter.description: Specifies the minimum jitter among all the iterations of the SAA.

alaSaaMacCtrlAvgJitter.name: alaSaaMacCtrlAvgJitter
alaSaaMacCtrlAvgJitter.description: Specifies the average jitter of all the iterations of the SAA.

alaSaaMacCtrlMaxJitter.name: alaSaaMacCtrlMaxJitter
alaSaaMacCtrlMaxJitter.description: Specifies the maximum jitter among all the iterations of the SAA.

alaSaaMacCtrlTSMinRTT.name: alaSaaMacCtrlTSMinRTT
alaSaaMacCtrlTSMinRTT.description: Specifies the timestamp of the iteration that gave the minimum packet delay.

alaSaaMacCtrlTSMaxRTT.name: alaSaaMacCtrlTSMaxRTT
alaSaaMacCtrlTSMaxRTT.description: Specifies the timestamp of the iteration that gave the maximum packet delay.

alaSaaMacCtrlTSMinJitter.name: alaSaaMacCtrlTSMinJitter
alaSaaMacCtrlTSMinJitter.description: Specifies the timestamp of the iteration that gave the minimum packet jitter.

alaSaaMacCtrlTSMaxJitter.name: alaSaaMacCtrlTSMaxJitter
alaSaaMacCtrlTSMaxJitter.description: Specifies the timestamp of the iteration that gave the maximum packet jitter.

alaSaaMacResultsTable.name: alaSaaMacResultsTable
alaSaaMacResultsTable.description: Defines the MAC-Ping Results Table for providing the capability of performing MAC-Ping operations. The results of these operations are stored in the alaSaaMacResultsTable and the alaSaaMacHistoryTable. An entry is removed from the alaSaaMacResultsTable when its corresponding alaSaaCtrlEntry is deleted.

alaSaaMacResultsEntry.name: alaSaaMacResultsEntry
alaSaaMacResultsEntry.description: Defines an entry in the alaSaaMacResultsTable. The alaSaaMacResultsTable has the same indexing as the alaSaaMacCtrlTable in order for a alaSaaMacResultsEntry to correspond to the alaSaaMacCtrlEntry that caused it to be created. An entry in this table summarizes results from multiple invocations of the test configured by the corresponding entry in alaSaaMacCtrlTable.

alaSaaMacResultsTestRunIndex.name: alaSaaMacResultsTestRunIndex
alaSaaMacResultsTestRunIndex.description: The value of alaSaaMacResultsTestRunIndex identifies the row entry that reports results for a single test run. The value of this object starts from 1 and can go upto a maximum of alaSaaCtrlMaxHistoryRows.

alaSaaMacResultsPktsSent.name: alaSaaMacResultsPktsSent
alaSaaMacResultsPktsSent.description: Specifies the number of packets sent during a single MAC-Ping iteration.

alaSaaMacResultsPktsRcvd.name: alaSaaMacResultsPktsRcvd
alaSaaMacResultsPktsRcvd.description: Specifies the number of packets received during a single MAC-Ping iteration

alaSaaMacResultsInterPktDelay.name: alaSaaMacResultsInterPktDelay
alaSaaMacResultsInterPktDelay.description: Specifies the inter-packet-delay with which the packets were sent in the iteration.

alaSaaMacResultsRunResult.name: alaSaaMacResultsRunResult
alaSaaMacResultsRunResult.description: The result of the MAC-Ping iteration.

alaSaaMacResultsRunResultReason.name: alaSaaMacResultsRunResultReason
alaSaaMacResultsRunResultReason.description: If the iteration fails, this field indicates the reason for failure. If the reason for failure cannot be determined the value of this field is the string Unknown. For successful iterations, the value of this field is the string 'Iteration successful'.

alaSaaMacResultsRunTime.name: alaSaaMacResultsRunTime
alaSaaMacResultsRunTime.description: The date and time at which the iteraton was run.

alaSaaMacHistoryTable.name: alaSaaMacHistoryTable
alaSaaMacHistoryTable.description: Defines a table for storing the results of a MAC-Ping iteration. The number of entries in this table for a configured test are limited by the value of the corresponding alaSaaCtrlMaxHistoryRows object. An entry in this table is created when the result of an MAC-Ping test is determined. An entry is removed from this table when its corresponding alaSaaMacCtrlEntry is deleted. The agent removes the oldest entry for a test in the alaSaaMacHistoryTable to allow the addition of a new entry for that test once the number of rows in the alaSaaMacHistoryTable reaches the value specified by alaSaaCtrlMaxHistoryRows.

alaSaaMacHistoryIndex.name: alaSaaMacHistoryIndex
alaSaaMacHistoryIndex.description: An entry in this table is created when the result of an MAC-ping iteration is determined. The initial 2 instance identifier index values identify the alaSaaMacCtrlEntry that an MAC-ping iteration result (alaSaaMacHistoryEntry) belongs to. The alaSaaMacHistoryIndex element selects a single ping iteration result. The value of this object starts from 1 and can go up to 20,history of first 20 packets will be stored.

alaSaaMacHistoryPktRTT.name: alaSaaMacHistoryPktRTT
alaSaaMacHistoryPktRTT.description: The round trip time taken by a single packet in an iteration.

alaSaaMacHistoryPktJitter.name: alaSaaMacHistoryPktJitter
alaSaaMacHistoryPktJitter.description: The jitter value for a single packet in an iteration.

alaSaaMacResultsPortTable.name: alaSaaMacResultsPortTable
alaSaaMacResultsPortTable.description: Defines a table for storing the results of ports for a MAC-Ping iteration. It only holds results from the last iteration.

alaSaaMacResultsPortChassis.name: alaSaaMacResultsPortChassis
alaSaaMacResultsPortChassis.description: The chassis number of the entry.

alaSaaMacResultsPortSlot.name: alaSaaMacResultsPortSlot
alaSaaMacResultsPortSlot.description: The slot number of the entry.

alaSaaMacResultsPortPort.name: alaSaaMacResultsPortPort
alaSaaMacResultsPortPort.description: The port number of the entry.

alaSaaMacResultsPortRTT.name: alaSaaMacResultsPortRTT
alaSaaMacResultsPortRTT.description: The round trip time taken by a single packet in an iteration.

alaSaaMacResultsPortMinRTT.name: alaSaaMacResultsPortMinRTT
alaSaaMacResultsPortMinRTT.description: The minimum round trip time taken by a single packet for the port.

alaSaaMacResultsPortMaxRTT.name: alaSaaMacResultsPortMaxRTT
alaSaaMacResultsPortMaxRTT.description: The maximum round trip time taken by a single for the port.

alaSaaMacResultsPortJitter.name: alaSaaMacResultsPortJitter
alaSaaMacResultsPortJitter.description: The jitter value for a single packet in an iteration.

alaSaaMacResultsPortMinJitter.name: alaSaaMacResultsPortMinJitter
alaSaaMacResultsPortMinJitter.description: The minimum jitter value for a single packet for the port.

alaSaaMacResultsPortMaxJitter.name: alaSaaMacResultsPortMaxJitter
alaSaaMacResultsPortMaxJitter.description: The maximum jitter value for a single packet for the port.

alaSaaXmlInterval.name: alaSaaXmlInterval
alaSaaXmlInterval.description: Interval where SAA will save the file. The value is in minutes.

alaSaaSpbAutoCreate.name: alaSaaSpbAutoCreate
alaSaaSpbAutoCreate.description: Determines if the SPB VLANs are automatically configured.

alaSaaSpbAutoStart.name: alaSaaSpbAutoStart
alaSaaSpbAutoStart.description: Determines if the SPB VLANs are automatically started.

alaSaaSpbInterval.name: alaSaaSpbInterval
alaSaaSpbInterval.description: Interval, in minutes, between two iterations of the SAA test. Valid values are 1, 2, 5 and 10-1500.

alaSaaSpbNumPkts.name: alaSaaSpbNumPkts
alaSaaSpbNumPkts.description: The number of packets to be sent in one iteration of Eth-LB/DMM test.

alaSaaSpbInterPktDelay.name: alaSaaSpbInterPktDelay
alaSaaSpbInterPktDelay.description: Specifies the delay between two consecutive packets transmitted during an iteration. The value specified should be a multiple of 100.

alaSaaSpbPayloadSize.name: alaSaaSpbPayloadSize
alaSaaSpbPayloadSize.description: Specifies the size of the MAC-Ping payload to be used for the MAC-Ping operation.

alaSaaSpbVlanPriority.name: alaSaaSpbVlanPriority
alaSaaSpbVlanPriority.description: Priority. 3 bit value to be used in the VLAN tag, if present in the transmitted frame.

alaSaaSpbDropEligible.name: alaSaaSpbDropEligible
alaSaaSpbDropEligible.description: Drop Enable bit value to be used in the VLAN tag, if present in the transmitted frame.

alaSaaSpbPktData.name: alaSaaSpbPktData
alaSaaSpbPktData.description: An arbitrary amount of data to be included in the Data TLV, if the Data TLV is selected to be sent.

alaSaaSpbJitterThreshold.name: alaSaaSpbJitterThreshold
alaSaaSpbJitterThreshold.description: Trap is generated when the Jitter Threshold is crossed. 0 indicates it is diabled.

alaSaaSpbRTTThreshold.name: alaSaaSpbRTTThreshold
alaSaaSpbRTTThreshold.description: Trap is generated when the RTT Threshold is crossed. 0 indicates it is diabled.

alaSaaSpbReset.name: alaSaaSpbReset
alaSaaSpbReset.description: When set TRUE, will set the alaSaaSpbFeature variables to the defualts.

alaSaaSpbKeep.name: alaSaaSpbKeep
alaSaaSpbKeep.description: When set on, SPB sessions will not be deallocated when SPB indicates a MAC or VLAN went away.

alaSaaSpbFlush.name: alaSaaSpbFlush
alaSaaSpbFlush.description: When set TRUE, SPB sessions will be flushed and reallocated with the current SPB MACs and VLANs.

alaSaaIPIterationCompleteTrap.name: alaSaaIPIterationCompleteTrap
alaSaaIPIterationCompleteTrap.description: A alaSaaIPIterationCompleteTrap notification is sent when a IP SAA iteration is completed.

alaSaaEthIterationCompleteTrap.name: alaSaaEthIterationCompleteTrap
alaSaaEthIterationCompleteTrap.description: A alaSaaEthIterationCompleteTrap notification is sent when a Eth-LB or Eth-DMM SAA iteration is completed.

alaSaaMacIterationCompleteTrap.name: alaSaaMacIterationCompleteTrap
alaSaaMacIterationCompleteTrap.description: A alaSaaIPIterationCompleteTrap notification is sent when a IP SAA iteration is completed.

alaSaaPacketLossTrap.name: alaSaaPacketLossTrap
alaSaaPacketLossTrap.description: A alaSaaPacketLossTrap notification is sent when a packet is lost during a test.

alaSaaJitterThresholdYellowTrap.name: alaSaaJitterThresholdYellowTrap
alaSaaJitterThresholdYellowTrap.description: A alaSaaJitterThresholdTrap notification is sent when 90% of the Jitter Threshold is crossed.

alaSaaRTTThresholdYellowTrap.name: alaSaaRTTThresholdYellowTrap
alaSaaRTTThresholdYellowTrap.description: A alaSaaRTTThresholdYellowTrap notification is sent when 90% of the RTT Threshold is crossed.

alaSaaJitterThresholdRedTrap.name: alaSaaJitterThresholdRedTrap
alaSaaJitterThresholdRedTrap.description: A alaSaaJitterThresholdTrap notification is sent when the Jitter Threshold is crossed.

alaSaaRTTThresholdRedTrap.name: alaSaaRTTThresholdRedTrap
alaSaaRTTThresholdRedTrap.description: A alaSaaRTTThresholdRedTrap notification is sent when the RTT Threshold is crossed.
